## Section 2. Terminology

- This draft re-uses the Terminology defined in [RFC8724] and the
- achitecture document.
+ This draft re-uses the terminology defined in [RFC8724] and in the SCHC
+ Architecture document [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture]. In particular,
+ Endpoint, Instance, Session, Context, and Set of Rules are used as
+ defined there.

- *  SCHC Core: SCHC End-Point located at the boundary of a regular IP
-    network and a network that applies SCHC compression and
-    fragmentation
+ *  SCHC Core: a SCHC Endpoint (as defined in
+    [I-D.ietf-schc-architecture]) located at the boundary of a regular IP
+    network and a network that applies SCHC compression and
+    fragmentation. It hosts the core-side Instance of the Session with the
+    SCHC Device. The SCHC Core MAY be co-located with an IP-router
+    function used to originate ICMPv6 messages (see Sections 6 and 7).

- *  SCHC Device: The other end of the SCHC instance formed with the
-    SCHC core.
+ *  SCHC Device: the SCHC Endpoint at the other end of the Session formed
+    with the SCHC Core; it hosts the Device-side Instance.

