## Section 7. Device is the destination of an ICMPv6 error message

- It should be compressed by the SCHC Core, but in the
- reverse direction.  New MOs and CDAs are introduced to perform this
- operation.  The MO check is a rule that matches the Target Value in
- the forward or reverse direction and the CDA performs this
- compression.
+ It should be compressed by the SCHC Core, but in the
+ reverse Direction.  New MOs and CDAs are introduced to perform this
+ operation.  The MO checks whether a Rule in the current Set of Rules
+ matches the Target Value in the forward or reverse Direction, and the
+ CDA performs this compression.

### Section 7.1. Matching Operator rule match and reverse rule match.

- If the Target Value contains a header, this matching operator returns
- True if a Rule exists in the current Set of Rule to compress it.  The
- selection can either be done:
+ If the Target Value contains a header, this Matching Operator returns
+ True if a Rule exists in the current Set of Rules to compress it.  The
+ selection can either be done:

- *  in the same direction of the End-Point, this can be used to
-    compress a protocol encapsulated in the header.
+ *  in the same Direction as the Endpoint, this can be used to
+    compress a protocol encapsulated in the header.

- *  in the reverse direction of the end point, as in an ICMPv6 error
-    message.
+ *  in the reverse Direction relative to the Endpoint, as in an ICMPv6
+    error message.

### Section 7.2. Compression Decompression Actions to compress Target Values.

- These CDAs compress-sent and rev-compress-sent compress the Target
- Value using rules defined in the current Set of Rules.  This CDA MUST
- be used in conjunction with the Matching Operators defined in
- Section 7.1 according to the direction.  The compression is using the
- same direction as the End-Point, the reverse compression uses the
- opposite direction.
+ These CDAs compress-sent and rev-compress-sent compress the Target
+ Value using Rules defined in the current Set of Rules.  This CDA MUST
+ be used in conjunction with the Matching Operators defined in
+ Section 7.1 according to the Direction.  The compression uses the
+ same Direction as the Endpoint; the reverse compression uses the
+ opposite Direction.

### Section 7.3. Example of ICMPv6 error message compression.

